README.md
     1‚Üí# Versioning Library for Go
     6‚Üígo-version is a library for parsing versions and version constraints,
     7‚Üíand verifying versions against a set of constraints. go-version
     8‚Üícan sort a collection of versions properly, handles prerelease/beta
     9‚Üíversions, can increment versions, etc.
    10‚Üí
    11‚ÜíVersions used with go-version must follow [SemVer](http://semver.org/).
    12‚Üí
    13‚Üí## Installation and Usage
    15‚ÜíPackage documentation can be found on
    16‚Üí[Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version).
    17‚Üí
    18‚ÜíInstallation can be done with a normal `go get`:
    19‚Üí
    20‚Üí```
    21‚Üí$ go get github.com/hashicorp/go-version
    22‚Üí```
    23‚Üí
